			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2016</a> keynote:</span><br><i>Redex: A Language for Lightweight Semantics Engineering</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/RobertBruceFindler.html">Robert Bruce Findler</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1145/2997364.2998391">10.1145/2997364.2998391</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t3a.html"><span class="tagM">T3A: Meta-languages</span></a><ul><li> Redex is a dedicated metalanguage for specifying grammars, type systems, and operational semantics.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1c.html"><span class="tagL">T1C: Behavioural Semantics</span></a><ul><li> It supports operational semantics engineering by executing and exploring semantic models.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1b.html"><span class="tagL">T1B: Static Semantics</span></a><ul><li> It includes support for specifying and checking type systems as part of the language models.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5c.html"><span class="tagL">T5C: Testing</span></a><ul><li> It uses random generation/testing to falsify semantic claims about models.
</li></ul></li></ul>
